Your Honor,

I stand before you to plead guilty to the offense of speeding. I acknowledge the gravity of my actions and the potential danger I posed to those around me. It was a lapse in judgment, driven by my curiosity to test the limits of my brand-new car. While I admit it was an exhilarating experience, I now understand the error of my ways and the potential consequences that could have resulted.

I must acknowledge that I failed to respond to the Notice of Intended Prosecution (NIP) that was sent to me. I deeply regret this oversight and want to make it clear that if I had been aware of its arrival, I would have promptly responded and taken responsibility for my actions. The fact that I did not see the NIP and subsequently failed to respond is something I am deeply remorseful for and I assure the court that it was not a deliberate attempt to evade the consequences of my actions.

In terms of my background, I am a 26-year-old individual with no criminal record aside from the driving offenses. I understand that my previous speeding incidents have incurred penalty points on my license, and I take full responsibility for my actions in those instances as well. However, I want to emphasize that apart from these driving offenses, I have conducted myself in a law-abiding manner and I ask that the court consider this aspect of my character.

Furthermore, I feel it is important to bring to your attention that I have ADHD. While I do not use it as an excuse for my behavior, I believe it is relevant in understanding the challenges I face in maintaining focus and making responsible decisions. I am actively seeking treatment and support for my condition to ensure I can better manage my impulses and make more responsible choices in the future.

I would also like to express my willingness to make amends for the harm my offense may have caused. I understand that actions speak louder than words, and I am committed to taking steps to prevent the repetition of such irresponsible behavior. I have already enrolled in a defensive driving course to further educate myself on safe driving practices, and I am exploring opportunities to raise awareness about the dangers of speeding within my community.

Finally, I want to express my sincere remorse for the distress and endangerment I caused through my actions. As I move forward, I am dedicated to becoming a more responsible and law-abiding citizen. I humbly request the court's leniency and ask for a fair and proportionate sentence that takes into account my plea of guilt and the mitigating factors presented.

Thank you for allowing me the opportunity to address the court.

Sincerely,

